title: Children participating in cricket in England 2010 to 2018
summary: This is a multi-line chart with 2 lines representing 5-10 years, and 11-15 years. The y axis denotes Share of respondents and the x axis denotes Year.
Overall 5-10 years, and 11-15 years are gradually decreasing,  throughout the Year
The ranking of the lines from topmost to botommmost is as follows: 1. 11-15 years, and lastly, 2. 5-10 years.
Overall across the Year, 11-15 years mostly maintained the highest Share of respondents when compared to others with a mean value of 17.7, and it peaked at 2012.
5-10 years mostly had the least Share of respondents with a mean value of 5.46, which peaked at 2011 with a value of 6.9.
